-- Ukraine Offers Its Carbon-Emission Permits to World Bank, Kommersant Says
-- Kateryna Choursina
-- 2010-09-20T07:33:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-20/ukraine-offers-its-carbon-emission-permits-to-world-bank-kommersant-says.html

          
          
             Ukraine has offered to sell its
entire supply of greenhouse gas emissions permits to the World
Bank,  Kommersant-Ukraine  newspaper reported, citing an
unidentified official.  
 The Ukrainian government wants to sell its 460 million
allowances at a price of 9 to 10 euros ($11.79-$13.10) each, the
newspaper cited the official as saying.  
 The World Bank has expressed interest in buying 2 million
to 3 million permits in 2011 at a price of 7.5 to 8.3 euros,
according to Kommersant.  
